node.text: London to New York in 3h flat on a good day with the Concorde. The Concorde always had priority during take-offs due to its fuel consumption, didn’t matter if was 30+ planes in queue the Concorde would always glide past first to the runway. 🍸

node.text:
Afghan babies passed over the wall at Kabul airport now being transported to Europe.

Here a Norwegian soldier cradles a baby on its way to Oslo in a military transport plane.
